# Page folder structure

Routes map to folders under `src/pages/`. The page component file is always `index.tsx`.

## Mapping

| Route | File |
|-------|------|
| `/` | `src/pages/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet` | `src/pages/alphabet/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/hiragana` | `src/pages/alphabet/hiragana/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/katakana` | `src/pages/alphabet/katakana/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise` | `src/pages/alphabet/exercise/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise/romaji` | `src/pages/alphabet/exercise/romaji/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise/character` | `src/pages/alphabet/exercise/character/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise/listen` | `src/pages/alphabet/exercise/listen/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise/script-pair` | `src/pages/alphabet/exercise/script-pair/index.tsx` |
| `/alphabet/exercise/writing` | `src/pages/alphabet/exercise/writing/index.tsx` |

## Course routes (generic pages, one folder each)

Course pages are shared and parameterized by `level: CourseLevel` (registered once in `src/app.tsx` by looping `COURSE_LEVELS` (`n5`-`n1`, `frontend`)). Each course page still gets its OWN folder with the page as `index.tsx` (one component = one folder):

| Route | File |
|-------|------|
| `/:level` | `src/pages/course/course-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/lesson/:lessonId` | `src/pages/course/lesson-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/lesson/:lessonId/exercise` | `src/pages/course/exercise-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/lesson/:lessonId/listening` | `src/pages/course/listening-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/lesson/:lessonId/reading` | `src/pages/course/reading-page/index.tsx` |

The frontend reference page is `src/pages/course/frontend-reference/index.tsx`.

## One folder per component / page (IMPORTANT)

- Every component and page lives in its own folder, with the component itself as `index.tsx` (e.g. `src/components/speak-button/index.tsx`, `src/pages/course/lesson-page/index.tsx`). Do NOT keep multiple sibling components as flat files in one folder.
- Import a component/page by its folder, extensionless: `import { SpeakButton } from '@/components/speak-button'` (resolves to `.../speak-button/index.tsx`).

## Colocation

- Put a helper used by only ONE page inside that page's folder (e.g. `course/exercise-page/course-quiz.ts`, `course/listening-page/course-listening.ts`). Reference it relatively as a sibling (`./course-quiz.ts`).
- A helper/component shared by SIBLING pages gets its own folder in the shared parent (e.g. `course/choice-button/index.tsx`, `course/shared/index.tsx` for `LessonNotFound`/`ResultScreen`), imported via `@/pages/course/...`.
- Shared code for a route segment stays in that segment folder (e.g. `alphabet/alphabet-chart.tsx` for hiragana + katakana).
- Globally reusable UI stays in `src/components/<name>/index.tsx`.
- Colocate a `*.test.ts(x)` next to the file it tests.

## New pages

When adding a route `/foo/bar`, create `src/pages/foo/bar/index.tsx` and register it in `src/constants/routes.ts` and `src/app.tsx`.

## Imports

Prefer `@/pages/...` and `@/components/...` path aliases (extensionless for folder-based components/pages). Use relative imports only for siblings in the same folder.
